  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this pilot study was to evaluate the effect of D-chiro-Inositol (DCI) oral
      supplementation in addiction to folic acid compared to folic acid alone on glycaemic control
      as assessed by HbA1c in overweight or obese T1D patients undergoing intensive insulin
      therapy.

      A 24 weeks, prospective, randomized control trial was carried out in T1D patients, aged 17-50
      years (13 males, 13 females), with disease duration &gt; 1 year and BMI &gt;25, attending as
      outpatients the Endocrinology and Diabetes Unit of University Campus Bio-Medico in Rome
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
